== Adding User Rules == <!--T:8-->

<!--T:9-->
Locate the directory "HTTPSEverywhereUserRules". It should be named something similar to {{Code2|/home/user/.tb/tor-browser/Browser/TorBrowser/Data/Browser/profile.default/HTTPSEverywhereUserRules/}}. 

<!--T:10-->
Create a new file called {{Code2|WhonixOnion.xml}}.

<!--T:11-->
{{Open_File|filename=
/home/user/.tb/tor-browser/Data/Browser/profile.default/HTTPSEverywhereUserRules/WhonixOnion.xml
}}

<!--T:12-->
For the v2 onion, paste. <ref>Users who want to force the v3 onion instead should replace the final rule line with <code><rule from="^https?://(.*\.?)whonix\.org/" to="http://$1http://dds6qkxpwdeubwucdiaord2xgbbeyds25rbsgr73tbfpqpt4a6vjwsyd.onion/"/></code></ref>
{{CodeSelect|code=
<ruleset name="Whonix Onion">
  <target host="whonix.org" />
  <target host="www.whonix.org" />
  <target host="phabricator.whonix.org" />
  <target host="forums.whonix.org" />
  <target host="download.whonix.org" />
  <target host="deb.whonix.org" />
  <rule from="^https?://(.*\.?)whonix\.org/" to="http://$1kkkkkkkkkk63ava6.onion/"/>
</ruleset>
}}
Save.

----
== (Re)Start Tor Browser == <!--T:13-->

<!--T:14-->
After installing the user rule, start or restart Tor browser. When navigating to www.whonix.org, HTTPS Everywhere will automatically engage and instead send the user to kkkkkkkkkk63ava6.onion or dds6qkxpwdeubwucdiaord2xgbbeyds25rbsgr73tbfpqpt4a6vjwsyd.onion, depending on the rule that was set. To disable this functionality, disable the ruleset using the HTTPS Everywhere icon in the upper right of the browser window, or simply delete the file.

<!--T:15-->
Happy browsing!

